{{Quote|Contractors, READ THIS FIRST! Use the Thorium charges in this locker only as a last resort to clear a blocked door. This structure is very old and unstable, and cave-ins could damage or destroy the artifacts we were sent here to collect.|[[Datapad/Legends|Datapad]] found by the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]] on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
'''[[Thorium/Legends|Thorium]] charges''' were high-explosives used for demolitions. A thorium charge was more powerful than a comparably-sized [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]].

[[Akkere]] had some in his possession in [[3951 BBY]], and may have sold them to the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]]. Some were also carried by [[Scavenger/Legends|contractors]] who explored the [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith Academy]] on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]].

==Behind the scenes==
The player character in ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]'' can obtain thorium charges from Akkere through dialogue near the end of the [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] mission or by killing the merchant, and can find them on Korriban accompanied by a datapad highlighting their destructive nature. The charges are in a nearby footlocker, and if the player character chooses to "bash open" the footlocker instead of cracking its lock, the thorium charges detonate, causing damage to all party members nearby.

